SOFTWARE TESTING

>> sw works as per user req

>> disadvantages of manual TESTING
--time consuming
--tedious, monotonous
--req consistency
--chances of human err due to dependency on manpower
--cost is only init less

>> automation TESTING
--uses testing tools/tech
--write script once, run many times

--ADVANTAGES
--faster exec
--less people req
--accuracy
--improved consistency
--reusability

--disadvantages
--programming knowledge req
--high init cost
--technical issues
--fails in cases where human judgement is req

COMPONENTS/TOOLS OF SELENIUM:
--Selenium -> 2004, jason Huggins
--Sel. RC 2004 ..Remote control -->req RC server separately installed is bw script and web -->complex -->DEPRECATED
--Sel. Web driver 2009-->overcome the server problem --> Doesn't allow parallel execution -->Only for web appln -->no 100% automation -->no customer support
--Sel. IDE 2006-->Record and Playback tool -->replays the action performed -->actions get recorded and played when required -->not apt for data driven testing
--Sel. Grid 2011--> overcomes the parallel execution problem -->hub node architecture


